# Claude Code / second-shift local session telemetry — per-run audit hook logs.
# Never version-controlled: machine-local, regenerated each run, pure noise in diffs.
.claude/audit/

# dev-pipeline run state — machine-local per-ticket state files (incl. this repo's
# own canary/dogfooding runs). Transient; the default paths.pipelineStateDir.
.claude/pipeline-state/

# dev-pipeline linked worktrees — the pipeline creates its own git worktrees here
# (Stage-2 work branches, Stage-1 intake-pin, config default topology.repos.<host>.worktreesDir).
# Machine-local and registered as git worktrees, but an untracked entry here still makes
# `git status --porcelain` non-empty, which mis-records the Stage-1 pre-flight attestation
# (workingTreeClean) on this repo's own dogfooding runs. Ignore it so the pipeline's own
# artifacts never read as a dirty tree. (Surfaced by the #1 dogfooding retro.)
.claude/worktrees/

# Per-machine direnv env (OTel telemetry export for cost tracking) — local-only,
# opt-in per engineer; see the dev-pipeline plugin's cost-tracking-setup.md.
.envrc
